explanation: The key observation is that the operation can be used to set any bit in `nums[i]` to 0, but not to 1. Therefore, the maximum possible bitwise XOR of all elements is achieved when all bits that are 1 in any of the numbers are set to 1 in the result. This is done by performing a bitwise OR operation on all numbers in the array.

